          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "SwiftDocCUtilities provides a default, command-line workflow for DocC, powered by Swift ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/apple.github.io\/swift-argument-parser\/documentation\/argumentparser\/",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ". ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "docc",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " commands, such as ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "convert",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "preview",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", are conformant ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/SwiftDocCUtilities\/documentation\/SwiftDocCUtilities\/Action",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " types that use DocC to perform documentation tasks.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Use SwiftDocCUtilities to build a custom, command-line interface and extend it with additional commands. To add a new sub-command called ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "example",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", create an conformant ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/SwiftDocCUtilities\/documentation\/SwiftDocCUtilities\/Action",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " type, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "ExampleAction",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", that performs the desired work, and add it as a sub-command. Optionally, you can also reuse any of the provided actions like ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/SwiftDocCUtilities\/documentation\/SwiftDocCUtilities\/ConvertAction",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "import ArgumentParser",
            "",
            "public struct MyDocumentationTool: ParsableCommand {",
            "    public static var configuration = CommandConfiguration(",
            "        abstract: \"My custom documentation tool\",",
            "        subcommands: [ConvertAction.self, ExampleAction.self]",
            "    )",
            "    ",
            "    public init() {",
            "    }",
            "}",
            "",
            "MyDocumentationTool.main()"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Adding a new sub-command automatically adds routing and execution of its code, adds its description to the command-line help menu, and ensures validation for its expected arguments.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
